Kọ́lá Túbọ̀sún is a Nigerian linguist, writer, scholar and cultural activist  whose work and influence span the fields of education, technology, literature, journalism, and linguistics. He is a Fulbright Fellow (Southern Illinois University Edwardsville, 2009) and recipient of the Premio Ostana "Special Prize" for Mother Tongue Literature 2016. He writes in Yoruba and English.
